<li id="cite_note-Merchant.27s_War-41"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Merchant.27s_War_41-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Merchant.27s_War_41-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text">A belated sequel, <i>The Merchants' War</i> (1984) was written by Pohl alone, after Kornbluth's death. Pohl's <i><a href="/wiki/The_Merchants_of_Venus" title="The Merchants of Venus">The Merchants of Venus</a></i> was an unconnected 1972 novella that includes biting satire on runaway <a href="/wiki/Free_market" title="Free market">free market</a> <a href="/wiki/Capitalism" title="Capitalism">capitalism</a> and first introduced the <a href="/wiki/Heechee" title="Heechee">Heechee</a>.</span></li>
